=========================================
LLD CHEAT SHEET (DESIGN PATTERNS + CORE IDEAS)
=========================================

========================
1. CREATIONAL PATTERNS (OBJECT CREATION)
========================

🔹 Singleton
- One class → ONE object
- global access point

Use when:
✔ logger
✔ config manager

Key idea:
class has private constructor + static getInstance()

-----------------------------------------

🔹 Factory
- Creates objects without exposing logic

Use when:
✔ runtime object creation

Key idea:
Client → Factory → Product

-----------------------------------------

🔹 Abstract Factory
- Factory of factories

Use when:
✔ multiple related object families

Example:
Windows UI vs Mac UI

-----------------------------------------

🔹 Builder
- Step-by-step object creation

Use when:
✔ complex object construction

Key idea:
Director → Builder → Product

=========================================
2. STRUCTURAL PATTERNS (OBJECT STRUCTURE)
=========================================

🔹 Adapter
- Converts one interface → another

Use when:
✔ incompatible APIs integration

Example:
charger adapter

-----------------------------------------

🔹 Decorator
- Adds features dynamically

Use when:
✔ extend behavior without inheritance

Example:
coffee + milk + sugar layers

-----------------------------------------

🔹 Facade
- Simplified interface to complex system

Use when:
✔ hide subsystem complexity

-----------------------------------------

🔹 Proxy
- Controls access to object

Use when:
✔ security
✔ caching
✔ lazy loading

=========================================
3. BEHAVIORAL PATTERNS (OBJECT INTERACTION)
=========================================

🔹 Observer
- One-to-many dependency

Use when:
✔ event systems

Example:
YouTube notifications

-----------------------------------------

🔹 Strategy
- Swap algorithms at runtime

Use when:
✔ remove if-else logic

Example:
payment methods (UPI/card/cash)

-----------------------------------------

🔹 Command
- Encapsulate request as object

Use when:
✔ undo/redo systems

=========================================
4. LLD CORE PRINCIPLES (VERY IMPORTANT)
=========================================

✔ Encapsulation → hide data
✔ Abstraction → show only required details
✔ Inheritance → reuse behavior
✔ Polymorphism → runtime behavior change

-----------------------------------------

SOLID PRINCIPLES:

S - Single Responsibility
O - Open/Closed
L - Liskov Substitution
I - Interface Segregation
D - Dependency Inversion

=========================================
5. MOST ASKED INTERVIEW PATTERNS (TOP PRIORITY)
=========================================

🔥 Singleton (MUST CODE)
🔥 Factory (MUST EXPLAIN + UML)
🔥 Observer (EVENT SYSTEM)
🔥 Adapter (REAL WORLD USE)
🔥 Decorator (EXTENSION WITHOUT INHERITANCE)

=========================================
6. LLD INTERVIEW FLOW (VERY IMPORTANT)
=========================================

When asked design question:

STEP 1:
→ Identify objects (classes)

STEP 2:
→ Define relationships
   (has-a / is-a)

STEP 3:
→ Choose patterns if needed

STEP 4:
→ Draw UML (simple boxes + arrows)

STEP 5:
→ Write APIs (functions)

STEP 6:
→ Explain scalability

=========================================
7. QUICK UML MEMORY RULE
=========================================

Arrow meanings:

→ uses
→ inherits
→ contains

Client → Service → Implementation

